    <section id="overview">
      <h2>{{ yearData.year }}: Year of the {{ yearData.element }} {{ yearData.animal }}</h2>
      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-card">
          <span class="info-card-icon">{{ yearData.animalEmoji }}</span>
          <div class="info-card-value">{{ yearData.animalCn }}</div>
          <div class="info-card-label">{{ yearData.animal }}</div>
          <div class="info-card-desc">Zodiac animal for {{ yearData.year }}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <span class="info-card-icon">
            {%- if yearData.element == "Wood" %}🌳{% elif yearData.element == "Fire" %}🔥{% elif yearData.element == "Earth" %}🏔️{% elif yearData.element == "Metal" %}⚔️{% elif yearData.element == "Water" %}💧{% endif -%}
          </span>
          <div class="info-card-value">{{ yearData.element }}</div>
          <div class="info-card-label">{{ yearData.elementCn }} &middot; {{ yearData.yinYang }}</div>
          <div class="info-card-desc">Heavenly Stem: {{ yearData.stem }}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <span class="info-card-icon">📅</span>
          <div class="info-card-value">{{ yearData.year }}</div>
          <div class="info-card-label">Gregorian Year</div>
          <div class="info-card-desc">Chinese zodiac year begins at Lichun (立春)</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>{{ yearData.year }} is the <strong>Year of the {{ yearData.element }} {{ yearData.animal }}</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">{{ yearData.elementCn }}{{ yearData.animalCn }}</span>) in the Chinese zodiac. This is a <strong>{{ yearData.yinYang }} {{ yearData.element }}</strong> year, governed by the Heavenly Stem <strong>{{ yearData.stem }}</strong>.</p>

      <p>In the traditional Chinese calendar, the zodiac year does not begin on January 1st. The Chinese zodiac year in BaZi (Four Pillars of Destiny) tradition starts at <strong>Lichun (立春)</strong>, the "Start of Spring" solar term, which typically falls on February 3rd, 4th, or 5th. People born before Lichun in {{ yearData.year }} belong to the previous zodiac year.</p>

      <div class="callout-box" style="margin:var(--sp-xl) 0;">
        <span class="callout-box-icon">🔮</span>
        <div class="callout-box-content">
          <h4>Find Your Exact Zodiac Animal</h4>
          <p>Born near the Chinese New Year boundary? Use our <a href="/zodiac/">zodiac calculator</a> with your full birth date to determine your exact zodiac animal, accounting for the Lichun solar boundary.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="element">
      <h2>{{ yearData.element }} Element ({{ yearData.elementCn }}) in {{ yearData.year }}</h2>
      <p>The {{ yearData.element }} element combines with the {{ yearData.animal }}'s fixed element to create the unique energy signature of {{ yearData.year }}. In Wu Xing (Five Elements) theory, {{ yearData.element }} interacts with the {{ yearData.animal }}'s innate qualities to produce distinct personality characteristics for people born in this year.</p>

      <p>The <strong>{{ yearData.element }} {{ yearData.animal }}</strong> carries <strong>{{ yearData.yinYang }}</strong> polarity. In Chinese cosmology, {{ yearData.yinYang }} energy represents {% if yearData.yinYang == "Yang" %}active, expansive, and outward-directed force — initiative, leadership, and bold action{% else %}receptive, inward, and reflective force — diplomacy, intuition, and careful cultivation{% endif %}.</p>

      <p>Learn more about how the Five Elements shape personality and destiny in our <a href="/wuxing/">Wu Xing encyclopedia article</a>{% if yearData.element == "Wood" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/wood/">Wood element page</a>{% elif yearData.element == "Fire" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/fire/">Fire element page</a>{% elif yearData.element == "Earth" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/earth/">Earth element page</a>{% elif yearData.element == "Metal" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/metal/">Metal element page</a>{% elif yearData.element == "Water" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/water/">Water element page</a>{% endif %}.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="personality">
      <h2>{{ yearData.animal }} Personality Traits</h2>
      <p>People born in the Year of the {{ yearData.animal }} (<span class="chinese-char">{{ yearData.animalCn }}</span>) share core zodiac traits that are modulated by the {{ yearData.element }} element. For a comprehensive analysis of {{ yearData.animal }} personality, compatibility, career strengths, and cultural significance, see our full <a href="/zodiac/{{ yearData.slug }}/">{{ yearData.animal }} zodiac profile</a>.</p>

      <p>The {{ yearData.element }} {{ yearData.animal }} of {{ yearData.year }} has distinct characteristics compared to other elemental variations of the {{ yearData.animal }}. The {{ yearData.element }} influence {% if yearData.element == "Wood" %}adds growth-oriented vision, flexibility, and creative idealism{% elif yearData.element == "Fire" %}amplifies passion, charisma, and bold expressiveness{% elif yearData.element == "Earth" %}brings stability, pragmatism, and grounded reliability{% elif yearData.element == "Metal" %}sharpens determination, discipline, and principled resolve{% elif yearData.element == "Water" %}deepens intuition, adaptability, and emotional intelligence{% endif %} to the {{ yearData.animal }}'s core nature.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="compatibility">
      <h2>Compatibility for {{ yearData.year }} {{ yearData.animal }}</h2>
      <p>Zodiac compatibility in Chinese astrology is determined by the animal sign, not the element. The {{ yearData.animal }}'s key compatibility relationships include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>San He (三合) — Zodiac Trio:</strong> The {{ yearData.animal }} forms a harmonious triad with two other animals, creating natural cooperation and shared goals.</li>
        <li><strong>Liu He (六合) — Secret Friend:</strong> The {{ yearData.animal }} has a "secret friend" pairing that creates deep, intuitive understanding.</li>
        <li><strong>Six Clash (六衝):</strong> The animal directly opposite on the zodiac wheel may create tension but also complementary growth.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Use our <a href="/compatibility/">compatibility checker</a> to explore your specific relationship dynamics, or read the full <a href="/zodiac/{{ yearData.slug }}/">{{ yearData.animal }} compatibility guide</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="bazi">
      <h2>{{ yearData.year }} in BaZi (Four Pillars)</h2>
      <p>In BaZi (八字) astrology, {{ yearData.year }} contributes the <strong>Year Pillar</strong> of <strong>{{ yearData.stem.split(' ')[0] }}-{{ yearData.animal }}</strong> ({{ yearData.stem.split(' ')[1] }}{{ yearData.animalCn }}) to your Four Pillars chart. The Year Pillar represents your relationship with society, your ancestral influence, and your public persona.</p>

      <p>For a complete BaZi analysis that includes all four pillars (Year, Month, Day, and Hour), use our <a href="/bazi-calculator/">BaZi calculator</a> or learn more about the <a href="/bazi/">Four Pillars of Destiny system</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="other-years">
      <h2>Other Years of the {{ yearData.animal }}</h2>
      <p>The {{ yearData.animal }} appears every 12 years in the zodiac cycle, but each occurrence carries a different element:</p>
      <div class="info-grid" style="margin-top:var(--sp-lg);">
        {%- set animalYears = zodiacYears | selectattr("animal", "equalto", yearData.animal) -%}
        {%- for y in animalYears -%}
        {%- if y.year != yearData.year %}
        <a href="/zodiac-year/{{ y.year }}/" class="info-card" style="text-decoration:none;{% if y.year == yearData.year %}border:2px solid var(--imperial-gold);{% endif %}">
          <div class="info-card-value">{{ y.year }}</div>
          <div class="info-card-label">{{ y.element }} {{ y.animal }}</div>
          <div class="info-card-desc">{{ y.elementCn }}{{ y.animalCn }} &middot; {{ y.yinYang }}</div>
        </a>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- endfor %}
